sql:
SELECT COUNT(bus_id) 
FROM bus_arrival_times 
WHERE delay > 5.0 AND season_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "highest average delays" implies the buses with the most significant delays compared to their usual performance;
- "overall average delay of all buses" is the average delay across all buses and all dates;
- "weather date" refers to the specific dates for which weather conditions were recorded.

sql:
SELECT day_id, AVG(delay) AS average_delay
FROM bus_arrival_times
GROUP BY day_id;

